About AHOF

AHOF (All Time Hall of Famer) is a 9-member global boy group formed through Universe League and set to debut under FNF Entertainment. Officially debuting on July 1, 2025, AHOF represents ambition, talent, and the pursuit of legendary status in the global music industry.

The name "All Time Hall of Famer" reflects the group's vision ‚Äî not just to succeed, but to leave a lasting legacy and become icons remembered for generations. With a diverse international lineup, AHOF showcases a powerful blend of cultures, skills, and personalities that connect with fans worldwide.

Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy explains how the AHOF Hall of Fame fan community website ("we," "us," or "the Site") collects, uses, stores, and protects information you share when using this platform. By participating in this community, you acknowledge and agree to the practices described below.

This policy is aligned with current global privacy standards including the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA/CPRA), and other applicable data protection frameworks as of 2026.

1. Information We Collect

We collect only the information you voluntarily provide when using this Site:

  • Usernames and display names ‚Äî entered when joining the Group Chat or submitting content. Once set, your username is permanently locked to your device.
  • Access code ‚Äî entered to gain access to the Members-Only Group Chat. The code itself is not stored on any server; only your approved status is saved locally in your browser.
  • Photos and images ‚Äî uploaded as voting proofs, posts, achievements, or chat images
  • Text content ‚Äî posts, achievement entries, chat messages, reactions, and notes you submit
  • Device identifier (UID) ‚Äî a randomly generated ID saved permanently to your browser's local storage to identify your device. This is used to lock your username and track your presence and reactions. It is not tied to your real identity.

We do not collect email addresses, phone numbers, payment details, or any sensitive personal data.

2. Group Chat ‚Äî How It Works

The FOHA Group Chat is a members-only feature with the following characteristics:

  • Access ‚Äî requires a valid username and the correct access code. The code is verified locally and never stored on any server.
  • Username lock ‚Äî once you choose a username and join the GC on a device, that username is permanently assigned to that device. It cannot be changed.
  • Member registry ‚Äî your username is permanently saved in our Firebase database as part of the GC member list. This allows all members to see who has joined the community.
  • Presence ‚Äî while you are active in the GC, your username appears in the "online" list. This is removed automatically when you leave or close the page.
  • Reactions ‚Äî emoji reactions you place on messages are stored in Firebase along with your username, visible to all GC members.
  • Message history ‚Äî all messages are stored in Firebase and visible to all GC members, including those who join later (full backread available).
  • Unsend ‚Äî you may delete your own messages at any time. Admins may also delete any message.

3. Browser Notifications

When you join the Group Chat, the Site may request permission to send browser notifications. If granted, you will receive notifications when new messages arrive while you are not viewing the GC. This permission is entirely optional ‚Äî you may deny it without affecting your ability to use the chat. You can revoke this permission at any time in your browser settings. Notification content (sender name and message preview) is processed locally by your browser and is not transmitted to any third party.

4. How We Use Your Information

  • To display community-submitted content (posts, achievements, voting proofs, chat messages, reactions) to authorized members and visitors
  • To enable real-time features such as the Members-Only Group Chat, online presence, and reactions
  • To maintain a permanent member registry showing who has joined the GC community
  • To allow you to unsend your own messages and manage your content
  • To send browser notifications for new GC messages (only if you grant permission)

We do not use your information for advertising, profiling, automated decision-making, or any commercial purpose.

5. Third-Party Services

This Site uses the following third-party platforms to operate:

  • Google Firebase (Realtime Database & Storage) ‚Äî stores messages, reactions, member registry, presence data, posts, achievements, and voting proofs. Governed by Google's Privacy Policy.
  • Cloudinary ‚Äî used for image hosting and delivery. Governed by Cloudinary's Privacy Policy.

This Site also contains links to official AHOF social media platforms:

  • Instagram, X (Twitter), TikTok, Facebook ‚Äî governed by their respective privacy policies
  • Weverse ‚Äî governed by Weverse's Privacy Policy (Hybe)
  • Weibo ‚Äî governed by Weibo's Privacy Policy

Clicking any external link takes you to a third-party platform. We are not responsible for how those platforms handle your data. Data stored in Firebase may be processed on servers outside your country. Google maintains Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) for international data transfers in compliance with GDPR.

6. Public Visibility

Content submitted in public sections ‚Äî including posts, achievements, and voting proofs ‚Äî is visible to all visitors. Group Chat messages, reactions, and the member list are visible only to users who have joined with the correct access code. Please only share content you are comfortable making available to the GC community.

7. Local Storage & Device Data

This Site stores the following data in your browser's local storage: your GC username, device UID, access approval status, and admin status (if applicable). This data is stored only on your device. Your device UID and username are permanently assigned ‚Äî clearing local storage (via browser settings or browser console) will reset your device identity, allowing a new username to be set.

8. Data Retention

Content you submit (posts, chat messages, voting proofs, images, reactions) remains stored in our Firebase database unless you delete it yourself (unsend) or request removal through an admin. Member registry entries are permanent records. We do not have an automatic deletion schedule.

9. Your Rights

Depending on your location, you may have the following rights:

  • Right to Access ‚Äî request a copy of information we hold about you
  • Right to Deletion ‚Äî request removal of your content or data, including your member registry entry
  • Right to Correction ‚Äî request that inaccurate information be corrected
  • Right to Withdraw Consent ‚Äî you may stop using the Site and request deletion of your submissions at any time

To exercise any of these rights, contact the Site administrators.

10. Children's Privacy

This Site is intended for general audiences. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If you believe a minor has submitted personal data without parental consent, please contact us immediately.

11. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Continued use of the Site after changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.

Last updated: February 2026  ¬∑  Aligned with GDPR (EU), CCPA/CPRA (California), and global privacy standards applicable as of 2026.
